    <ab>To this <em>wāz-gīrišnīh</em> could refer the Nērang ī Āb, when it refers to the last <em>wāz-gīrišnīh</em> of the pressing of <em>hōm</em> as the fifth passage during whose recitation the <em>zōt</em> has to gaze at the <em>āb</em> and <em>gōmēz</em>:</ab>
    <ab class="ab_indent">
    <em>panzōm pad ān ī wāz-gīrišnīh ī pad hom-kōftan sar hamāg xūb be nigērišnn</em>
    </ab>
    <ab class="ab_indent">
    The fifth is the <em>wāz-gīrišnīh</em> at the end of the <em>hōm</em>-pressing (VVrs31.0)". There he have to gaze carefully at all implements
